## Operational Cadence

What the agent checks and when. Each job reads the relevant skill file and runs
with tenant, brain, and source scope.

### Every Message

- Signal detection: `skills/signal-detector/SKILL.md`
- Brain-first lookup: `skills/conventions/brain-first.md`

### Morning

- Daily task prep: `skills/daily-task-prep/SKILL.md`
- Calendar lookahead
- Open threads from yesterday

### Every 15 Minutes

- Brain sync: `cortex sync --no-pull && cortex embed --stale`
- Provider queue check: `cortex jobs status --json`

### Daily

- Runtime manifest check: `cortex runtime manifest --json`
- Invite delivery drain health
- Integration webhook health

### Weekly

- Brain health: `cortex doctor --json`
- Embedding coverage: `cortex embed --stale`
- Citation audit: `skills/citation-fixer/SKILL.md`
- Back-link check: `cortex check-backlinks check`
- Brain lint: `cortex lint`

## Quiet Hours

- Default: 11 PM - 8 AM local time
- Override: tenant activity flag
- During quiet hours: save output to the held queue, release on first morning contact
- Exception: genuinely urgent alerts that would cause customer impact

## Schedule Staggering

Jobs should be offset by 5-minute intervals to avoid a thundering herd:

- `:00` reserved
- `:05`, `:10`, `:15`, `:20`, `:25`, `:30`, `:35`, `:40`, `:45`, `:50`
- max 1 concurrent job per minute unless the tenant plan allows more
